{"id": 232095506, "title": "Armed police and bomb squad descend on Leeds road as locals told 'stay indoors", "text": "Armed police have flooded a housing estate in Leeds. Locals have reportedly been warned to stay inside their homes in Stanningley following concerns for people at a property. A huge emergency presence is at the scene including armoured vehicles and Yorkshire Ambulance service. According to reports, police rushed to the Half Mile Green area in the late afternoon. Residents said that the authorities had been in the area for a couple of hours. Footage that has emerged online showed armed cops descend onto the street. There are also several marked police vehicles and ambulance incident units at the scene. It is understood that local residents have also be warned to stay indoors as the operation is carried out. One man, who said he lives down the road, told Leeds Live: \u201cThey\u2019ve just said it\u2019s an incident they won\u2019t say anything else.\u201d He says it\u2019s usually a quiet road and police have been here a couple of hours.\" According to Yapp News, dozens of police are present at the scene. They posted on Twitter: \"Residents asked to stay indoors after armed operation continues on a housing estate in Leeds. Dozens of armed officers and counterterror police remain at the scene in Stanningley this evening amid concerns for persons within a property. \"Half Mile Green, in the Stanningley area of the city is the subject of a huge emergency service incident where specialist firearms officers and trained negotiators deal with the incident. Yorkshire Ambulance have their incident response team at the scene supporting.\" A spokesperson for West Yorkshire Police said: \"A police operation is currently ongoing at an address in Half Mile Green, Stanningley. At 12.36pm today, officers were called to a domestic-related incident at the property but withdrew on seeing a male at the address in possession of what appeared to be a handgun. \"A cordon is currently in place and various emergency service resources, including police negotiators, are at the scene working to bring the incident to a safe conclusion. The male is the only person in the address and there is no risk to the wider community.\" This is a breaking news story. Follow us on Google News, Flipboard, Apple News, Twitter, Facebook or visit The Mirror homepage.", "summary": "A huge police presence has been reported at a housing estate in Leeds with armed police, armoured vehicles and a street sealed off in Stanningley - locals have reportedly been told to stay inside their homes", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/breaking-armed-police-bomb-squad-32993413", "image": "https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article32993444.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_PAY-Screenshot-2024-06-09-at-180052JPG.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 17:14:37", "author": "Monica Charsley,Monica-Charsley", "authors": ["Monica Charsley", "Monica-Charsley"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.34}